text: Dendropsophus rozenmani is a frog that lives in Bolivia. This frog lives in temporary and permanent bodies of water. It also lives in grasslands that have been flooded. The adult male frog is 18.7–21.1 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog is 19.6–23.2 mm long. The frog is brown in color with two dark brown stripes from its head to its middle. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Dendropsophus rozenmani
